First we need to install ffmpeg to start this process.
downlaod ffmpeg from here: https://www.ffmpeg.org/
extract the zip file in programs files folder..
open the bin folder, copy the path of bin folder.
goto the environment variables, create a new path, paste the copied path of bin directory save the path.
now open the CMD in the required folder.
check whether ffmpeg is working or not by giving command "ffmpeg".
Here is the command for merging audio with video: ffmpeg -i video.mp4 -i audio.wav -c:v copy -c:a aac output.mp4
replace the video.mp4 with your video file, make sure your file don't have any spaces.
replace the audio.wav with your audio file.
replace the output.mp4 with the name you want to give to your output file.
hit enter,
it will merge the audio and video in seconds.
